Definition: the state of inactivity following an interruption
Example: the negotiations were in arrest; held them in check; during the halt he got some lunch; the momentary stay enabled him to escape the blow; he spent the entire stop in his seat
Synonyms: check, verb, motion, change, halt, hitch, stay, stop, stoppage, inaction, the, state, of, inactivity, following, an, interruption, negotiations, were, in, held, them, during, he, got, some, lunch, momentary, enabled, him, to, escape, blow, spent, entire, his, seat
Category: noun.state
